8.  Website developer (1 position, 18 person-months). The website developer, preferably 
with 8 years of relevant work experience, will help the project leader and/or TA members 
expand,  improve,  and  operate  the  ARIC  website.  The  website  developer  will  work  on  an 
intermittent basis at ADB headquarters and will report to the principal economic analyst, project 
leader, and/or other TA members. Under the supervision of the project leader and/or other TA 
members, the website developer will 
(i)  design and improve the navigational tools using state-of-the-art technologies to 
improve user access across various content areas of the website; 
(ii)  build and maintain an efficient CMS to track and manage content, including text 
and graphics published on the ARIC website; 
(iii)  build highly interactive interfaces, a geo-data mapper, and charting components 
for  the macroeconomic  and financial  indicators  database  and  the  integration 
indicators database, and a comparative tool kit for the FTA database; 
(iv)  manage image galleries, podcasts, and video feeds; 
(v)  implement a tracking system to monitor ARIC website statistics; 
(vi)  conceptualize and execute designs for new uploads, and suggest modifications 
in page design; 
(vii)  analyze program specification and design, implement programs to generate links 
and web pages, and test and debug the programs; 
(viii)  maintain or modify programs to revise and update the contents of the improved 
ARIC website; 
(ix)  develop new concepts to simplify the ARIC website updating procedures; 
(x)  update and check entire database for errors, and manage the file structure of the 
entire website; 
(xi)  promote daily updates on the development and global websites; 
(xii)  prepare technical documentation for the improved ARIC website; 
(xiii)  conceptualize  and  develop  compact  disc  brochures  and  portable  database 
applications; 
(xiv)  conduct usability testing to evaluate and measure the website’s ease of use; and 
(xv)  provide other information technology support as may be requested by the project 
leader and/or other TA members.
